                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, July 30: The Securities and Exchange Board of India today allowed exchanges to introduce currency options on dollar pairing with rupee, a development that provides another alternative to corporate houses for hedging against currency fluctuations. According to a Sebi circular, only dollar-rupee contracts of $1,000 size would be allowed.                            
	 Mumbai, July 30: Hindustan Construction Company Ltds (HCC) subsidiary Lavasa Corporation is planning to raise Rs 2,000 crore through an initial public offer. The announcement came on a day when the company declared a 1:1 bonus issue.                             
	 Calcutta, July 30: The Rs 3,300-crore power infrastructure firm Thermax Ltd will spend Rs 500 crore in capital expenditure and to raise its stake in two joint           
	tures.                                                                                                                          
